  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I give my girlfriend space / stop the feeling of having my soul sucked out for the seconds I'm not with her?",
  "response": "It sounds like you're experiencing a mix of attachment and possibly dependency in your relationship. Here are some steps you can take to give your girlfriend space while also taking care of your own emotional well-being:\n\n1. **Reflect on Your Feelings**: Take some time to understand why you feel drained when you're apart. Are you feeling insecure, anxious, or overly reliant on her presence for happiness? Identifying these feelings can help you address the root cause.\n\n2. **Encourage Independence**: Encourage both yourself and your girlfriend to pursue individual interests and friendships. This can help both of you grow independently, which is healthy for any relationship.\n\n3. **Establish Boundaries**: Discuss openly with her about needing some personal space. Setting clear expectations about alone time can help both of you feel more comfortable.\n\n4. **Engage in Hobbies**: Focus on activities that you enjoy or have always wanted to try. This will allow you to develop your own interests and can provide a refreshing distraction when you\u2019re apart.\n\n5. **Practice Mindfulness or Meditation**: Engaging in mindfulness techniques such as meditation, deep breathing, or yoga can help reduce feelings of anxiety and improve your emotional resilience.\n\n6. **Limit Communication Temporarily**: It might be helpful to take a break from constant texting or calling each other throughout the day. Establish a routine for when you check in with each other that feels comfortable for both.\n\n7. **Join Social Groups**: Connect with friends or join clubs/groups where you can meet new people. Expanding your social circle can help reduce the feeling of loneliness or anxiety when you\u2019re not with her.\n\n8. **Take Care of Yourself**: Focus on self-care by ensuring you prioritize your physical, mental, and emotional health. Eating well, exercising, and getting enough sleep can help you feel more balanced.\n\n9. **Communicate Openly**: Talk to your girlfriend about how you're feeling in a calm and honest way. Express your needs without blaming her, and invite her to share her thoughts and feelings too.\n\n10. **Consider Professional Help**: If these feelings persist and are affecting your quality of life, it may be worth talking to a therapist or counselor for additional guidance and support.\n\nRelationships are about balance, and it's important for both partners to feel secure and fulfilled individually while being together. Finding that balance can significantly enrich your relationship overall.",
